# Digital Marketing Analytics — Facebook & Google Ads

## Overview
Cross-platform analysis of Facebook Ads and Google Ads daily performance data 
using PostgreSQL. Focuses on spend efficiency, campaign reach, and return on 
marketing investment (ROMI).

## Dataset
- 4 tables: facebook_ads_basic_daily, google_ads_basic_daily, 
  facebook_adset, facebook_campaign
- Metrics: spend, impressions, reach, clicks, leads, value

## Questions Answered
1. Daily spend metrics (avg, max, min) for Facebook and Google separately
2. Top 5 days by total ROMI across both platforms
3. Weekly campaign with highest total value
4. Campaign with biggest monthly reach growth
5. Longest continuously running ad set across both platforms

## Skills Demonstrated
- CTEs (Common Table Expressions)
- Window Functions: LAG(), ROW_NUMBER()
- COALESCE, NULLIF for null handling
- UNION ALL for cross-platform data merging
- Gaps-and-islands algorithm for streak detection
- ROMI calculation logic
